ion for the jury was whether Defendants made LIBOR submissions that reflect=
ed something other than honestly held estimates of the rate Deutsche Bank w=
ould have accepted in order to borrow funds.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6The court st=
ated that =E2=80=9Cwhether Deutsche Bank could have borrowed funds=C2=A0at =
a submitted rate is not dispositive of the falsity of its LIBOR submissions=
.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0It ruled that the government was not required to prove "tha=
