e different amounts of principal. King testified that the cash desk would "=
borrow money every single day,=E2=80=9D=C2=A0and that "[t]here were periods=
 where I need to=C2=A0borrow some $20- to $25 billion a day." He said that =
"[o]ften it costs you=C2=A0more to borrow more cash than less cash," and th=
us loans in various principal=C2=A0amounts could be at varying rates of int=
erest.=C2=A0Similarly, Curtler testified that "there were days where there =
would have=C2=A0been a wide range of offered rates." He said that "[i]f two=
